column1: * The purpose of this file is to define the symbolic text for drafting document
* This file contains 6 columns: Symbolic-Text word, PDM attributes/  ERP file,
* The Symbolic-Text word column presents the name of the attribute
* The  PDM attributes/  ERP file column presents the name of the attribute
* This column is not to be translated.
* The Application column presents the application from which the data is taken from ( represented as a number)
* You can also use the name of the application but it needs to be the same as the name in the string table
* The Units column determines whether the parameter is unit dependent or not.
* 0= unit independent (same result for inch or mm) , 1= unit dependent ( different result for inch or mm)
* The Relocated is relevant only for the electrode application. This parameter detemines whether to display
the data of external electrods as N/R or to show the real values.
* 0=show real values, 1= show N/R string or another string that is defined in the string table.
* The Description column is optional and it describes the symbolic text parameter for documenatary.
* How to add a new attribute to the file ?
* 1) Add the symbolic text word to the first column. ( It can be a translated name)
* 2) Add the DM attribute name to the second column.( It must be in english-unless you translate the DM attributes names
* 3) Select the application from which you want to read the data.  1= View_data, 2 = Drafting, 3 =Modeling, 4 = Electrode
* 4) Select 1 in the fourth column if the parameter is unit dependent or 0 if the parameter is unit independent
* 5) Select 0 in the fifth column for general use. If the parameter is relevant to an external electrode
*     and the data might be incorrect then select 1
